Reasoning: 
- cs.IT (Information Theory) is likely because the paper deals with optimal power allocation and maximum sum-rate in wireless communication systems.
- cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) is likely because the paper focuses on multiuser OFDMA systems and delivery strategies of messages to multiple users.
- cs.MM (Multimedia) is likely because the paper discusses the transmission of common and individual messages to multiple users, which can involve multimedia content.
- cs.SY (Systems and Control) is likely because the paper develops an algorithm for optimal power allocation and considers the impact of channel estimation and interference cancellation on system performance.
- cs.LG (Machine Learning) is less likely but still possible because the paper may involve machine learning techniques for channel estimation or interference cancellation.
